  "body": "I believe I've identified a potential SQL injection vulnerability in the Data API (`proposer_payload_delivered`). The problem is with the `block_hash` filter. The value provided in the request is directly copied into the filters structure without any checks.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/flashbots/mev-boost-relay/blob/e7170b33ffcefe353dc46434cf76ac4165b5b9fe/services/api/service.go#L814-L818\r\n\r\nThen an argument map is created.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/flashbots/mev-boost-relay/blob/e7170b33ffcefe353dc46434cf76ac4165b5b9fe/database/database.go#L97-L103\r\n\r\nAs long as it's not empty, the value will be in the query string.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/flashbots/mev-boost-relay/blob/e7170b33ffcefe353dc46434cf76ac4165b5b9fe/database/database.go#L119-L121\r\n\r\nAnd then it's executed.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/flashbots/mev-boost-relay/blob/e7170b33ffcefe353dc46434cf76ac4165b5b9fe/database/database.go#L131-L138",
